# instructions.env
# Session log: outlook_rwa RWA reconciliation against production
# Branch: claude/function-pem-accounts-behavior-a5TmE
# Date: 2026-05-26
# Goal: bring this repo's SA (standardized) and AA (advanced) RWA totals into
#       agreement with the archived production data set.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# =============================================================================
# TASK 1 — Repo totals were LOWER than production (PR #7, merged)
# =============================================================================

INPUT_1="Both SA and AA RWA totals came out lower than production. A prior change
(PR #4) had added \"Other Assets (L2)\" to NON_CREDIT_RISK_PMF. The correct list
value is \"Other Assets L3\" (no parentheses); \"Other Assets (L2)\" should not be
in that list."

DIAGNOSIS_1="\"Other Assets (L2)\" is a credit-risk account (it is in PMF_ACCOUNTS).
NON_CREDIT_RISK_PMF force-zeroes an account's SA/AA RWA in calculate_sa_rwa /
calculate_aa_rwa, so listing \"Other Assets (L2)\" there dropped real RWA from
both totals and pulled the repo below production."

FIX_1="src/main/tools/constants.py — in NON_CREDIT_RISK_PMF, replace
\"Other Assets (L2)\" with \"Other Assets L3\" (revert of the PR #4 entry).
Effect: \"Other Assets (L2)\" again flows through the credit-risk waterfall and
contributes Balances * RWF, restoring SA and AA totals to match production."

OUTPUT_1="PR #7 — 'Restore Other Assets L3 in NON_CREDIT_RISK_PMF' — MERGED.
Verified: \"Other Assets (L2)\" no longer in NON_CREDIT_RISK_PMF, \"Other Assets L3\"
is; an \"Other Assets (L2)\" row yields non-zero RWA again; a true non-credit-risk
row (e.g. \"Trading Account Assets (L2)\") still zeroes."

# =============================================================================
# TASK 2 — Repo OVER-stated one slice; present-0 RWF handling (PR #8, merged)
# =============================================================================

INPUT_2="Screenshots: for Corporate Banking [L4] / Banking [L2] / NAM, production
reported SA RWA = 0 and AA RWA = 0, but the repo produced SA = 9,113 and
AA = 2,393. The variant account was \"Deposits with Banks (L2)\" (US, Quarter 4;
key 34669/28614 + US + Deposits with Banks (L2) + 4). 'This one specific value
did not populate in production; it was not a reported standardized or advanced
total, but this repository's code includes it.'"

QUESTION_2="Asked: should \"Deposits with Banks (L2)\" be zeroed everywhere (add to
NON_CREDIT_RISK_PMF) or only for this Corporate Banking / NAM slice?"

ANSWER_2="Neither. The real rule: production uses the FIRST PRESENT risk weight
factor even when it is 0. For this row the RWFs were key1 = 0, key2 = 0,
key3 = 0.209093978, key4 = 0. The repo was skipping the present zeros and
multiplying key3's 0.209... by the balance, giving 9,113. When computing SA/AA
RWA: if a key's RWF is present (even 0) use it; only skip values that are truly
null / None / empty."

DIAGNOSIS_2="src/main/tools/functions.py, _first_valid_rwf() called
.replace(0, np.nan) before .bfill(axis=1), converting present zeros into
'missing' and backfilling past them to the next non-zero key. This over-stated
RWA wherever an earlier key's RWF was a legitimate 0."

FIX_2="src/main/tools/functions.py — remove the .replace(0, np.nan) step in
_first_valid_rwf. pd.to_numeric(errors='coerce') already coerces
null/None/empty/non-numeric to NaN, so bfill skips exactly those while a present
0 is used as-is. One helper feeds both calculate_sa_rwa and calculate_aa_rwa, so
the single change fixes standardized and advanced RWA together. No constants
change: \"Deposits with Banks (L2)\" stays in PMF_ACCOUNTS as a genuine
credit-risk account whose RWF simply happens to be 0 at the matched key."

OUTPUT_2="PR #8 — 'Treat a present 0 RWF as valid in the waterfall' — MERGED.
Verified end-to-end through calculate_sa_rwa/calculate_aa_rwa:
  - key1=0, key2=0, key3=0.209 -> SA/AA RWA = 0 (was 9,113 / 2,393);
  - key1=NaN, key2=NaN, key3=0.209 -> still falls through to key3 (non-zero);
  - present non-zero key1 -> unchanged;
  - NON_CREDIT_RISK_PMF account -> still forced to 0."

# =============================================================================
# KEY REFERENCES
# =============================================================================

WATERFALL_HELPER="src/main/tools/functions.py::_first_valid_rwf"
RWA_CALCS="src/main/tools/functions.py::calculate_sa_rwa, calculate_aa_rwa"
ACCOUNT_LISTS="src/main/tools/constants.py::PMF_ACCOUNTS (credit-risk waterfall), NON_CREDIT_RISK_PMF (force RWA to 0)"
KEY_FORMAT="Key1 = Managed Segment L4 Id + Managed Geography L4 Descr + PMF Account L5 Descr + Quarter Id (functions.py::build_outlook_key_strings); waterfall keys 1->5 go specific->broad"
PIPELINE="step1_model_convergence.py builds the 5-key RWF waterfall and computes RWA; step2_outlook_rwa.py consumes step1 outputs and builds the upload templates"
